  "analyst_notes": "PLN is Indonesia's state-owned electricity monopoly controlling 98% of power distribution with ~76 GW system capacity (57% coal). Key characteristics: (1) Sovereign-linked credit (BBB) masks weak standalone (ba3/bb+) due to 30% subsidy dependence; (2) Young coal fleet (avg 12 years, 55% under 10 years) creates major stranded asset risk; (3) JETP participant but implementation gaps widening (Cirebon-1 retirement CANCELLED Dec 2024). B5 CREDIT ANALYSIS (FY2023 complete): D/EBITDA 5.32x (threshold <4.0x) FAIL, Interest Coverage 3.76x (threshold >2.5x) PASS, FFO/Debt 17.5% (threshold >20%) FAIL, Current Ratio 0.92x (threshold >1.0x) FAIL, Debt/Capital 52.6% (threshold <60%) PASS. Only 2/5 metrics pass - FAILS B5. ETCB expected outcomes: B1 FAIL (57% coal, young fleet, 10 GW under construction), B2 FAIL (CCE ~104% at $4/tCO2 given 160.55 MtCO2 emissions vs $6.2B EBITDA), B3 MARGINAL (coal PLF declining to 49%, RE competitive but integration issues), B4 FAIL (no SBTi, 2060 net-zero, clean CapEx only ~15%, JETP implementation failing), B5 FAIL (2/5 metrics). Expected score: 0-1/5 Lowest tier. KEY RISK: 13.3 GW coal cancellations overshadowed by 10 GW under construction and 16.6 GW captive coal (exempt from moratorium, tripled since 2019). Take-or-pay IPP contracts at 80% capacity factor vs actual 49% PLF create ongoing financial strain."
